So, now that you've got

30:11.140 --> 30:13.508
a medical degree burning
a hole in your pocket,

30:13.542 --> 30:14.976
how do you plan to spend it?

30:15.010 --> 30:17.745
WILLIAM:
Uh...

30:17.779 --> 30:22.717
If... if one really intended to, uh...

30:22.751 --> 30:27.088
pursue the...
the science of human sexuality...

30:27.122 --> 30:29.690
BARTON: Oh, don't start.
I thought we settled this.

30:29.725 --> 30:31.125
WILLIAM:
But if one did?

30:31.160 --> 30:32.460
BARTON:
Because one was deranged?

30:32.494 --> 30:34.095
WILLIAM:
One was determined, you know?

30:34.129 --> 30:37.765
How... How would one go about it?

30:37.799 --> 30:40.201
BARTON:
[ Chuckles ]

30:40.235 --> 30:43.538
WILLIAM:
Come on. H-Hypothetically.

30:43.572 --> 30:47.608
BARTON: Well, you'd need to be
out of short pants, for one thing.

30:47.643 --> 30:50.178
A young buck in his 20s
doing this kind of work,

30:50.212 --> 30:51.712
you'd look like a Peeping Tom.

30:51.747 --> 30:53.948
WILLIAM: [ Chuckles ]
So, how... How old?

30:53.982 --> 30:57.451
BARTON:
40 at least,

30:57.486 --> 31:03.191
and you'd need an established practice
at a world-class teaching hospital,

31:03.225 --> 31:04.892
something in a respectable field.

31:04.927 --> 31:06.294
WILLIAM:
Urology?

31:06.328 --> 31:07.995
BARTON:
Obstetrics.

31:08.030 --> 31:12.400
You'd also need a spick-and-span
image, a perfect family.

31:12.434 --> 31:15.469
That means a wife.

31:15.504 --> 31:18.005
If Caroline's kaput, you ought
to take a night off work.

31:18.040 --> 31:19.307
Ask a nurse to the pictures.

31:19.341 --> 31:21.409
- WILLIAM: Ugh.
- BARTON: No! Call it research.

31:21.443 --> 31:23.477
WILLIAM:
I'm... I'm waiting for the right girl.

31:23.512 --> 31:25.079
BARTON:
[ Chuckles ]

31:25.113 --> 31:26.647
Hey!

31:26.682 --> 31:28.082
VIVIAN:
Are we having hamburgers?

31:28.116 --> 31:30.818
BARTON:
Yes, we are.

31:30.852 --> 31:33.921
The world isn't kind to mavericks, Bill.

31:33.956 --> 31:38.125
You want to lead
an unconventional life,

31:38.160 --> 31:40.994
you got to learn to hide
in plain sight.

31:43.632 --> 31:46.867
WILLIAM: Chief of Police Duncan,
Archbishop Peter O'Reilly,

31:46.902 --> 31:49.070
David Anhauser, Wyatt Busch,

31:49.104 --> 31:52.006
Richard Amberg at the St. Louis Globe,

31:52.040 --> 31:54.008
and all seven members
of the board of trustees,

31:54.042 --> 31:55.676
starting with Donald Morris.

31:55.711 --> 31:58.379
VIRGINIA: And what are we
going to do with these names?

31:58.413 --> 32:00.982
WILLIAM:
In 12 years at Washington University,

32:01.016 --> 32:02.783
I've delivered 3,000 babies.

32:02.818 --> 32:05.486
I have given families
to the leading lights in this community,

32:05.520 --> 32:06.654
and now these men are gonna help me.

32:06.688 --> 32:08.122
[ Indistinct shouting ]

32:08.156 --> 32:10.124
VIRGINIA:
By?

32:10.158 --> 32:12.727
WILLIAM: I don't know yet, but
Scully will have to listen to them.

32:12.761 --> 32:14.829
They will remind Scully
of my value to this hospital.

32:14.863 --> 32:16.764
REPORTER: You told me
you would give me a quote.

32:16.798 --> 32:17.965
ETHAN: I told you to stay away
from my patient and this hospital.

32:18.000 --> 32:21.235
ETHAN:
How about I just call the police?!

32:23.639 --> 32:26.741
REPORTER:
You got a quote on the quad case?

32:26.775 --> 32:29.477
- WILLIAM: The what?
- REPORTER: Quads, here at the hospital.

32:29.511 --> 32:31.712
Considering this is the first
instance of quadruplets

32:31.747 --> 32:33.180
here at maternity hospital,

32:33.215 --> 32:39.387
what are the risks involved
with such a case, Dr...Masters?

32:39.421 --> 32:42.657
WILLIAM: She's a 30-year-old
primipara with quadruplets.

32:42.691 --> 32:44.425
This raises her odds
of placental abruption

32:44.459 --> 32:45.559
by a factor of 3,

32:45.594 --> 32:47.228
toxemia by a factor of 10.

32:47.262 --> 32:48.596
ETHAN:
Her blood pressure is stable.

32:48.630 --> 32:50.031
WILLIAM: She should have been
sectioned out days ago.

32:50.065 --> 32:51.599
Dr. Haas can watch the delivery
from the observation deck.

32:51.633 --> 32:53.100
ETHAN:
It is my fucking case!

32:53.135 --> 32:55.102
WILLIAM: Which you should never
have taken in the first place.

32:55.137 --> 32:57.271
This is high-risk surgery.
He's a fellow.

32:57.306 --> 32:59.640
BARTON: Which is exactly why I had
him call you in as his second.

32:59.675 --> 33:02.777
WILLIAM:
Well, that's the first I'm hearing of it.

33:05.714 --> 33:06.847
ETHAN:
You don't have enough to do?

33:06.882 --> 33:10.518
You have to come in here
and steal my patient?

33:10.552 --> 33:12.119
I can handle this delivery.

33:12.154 --> 33:13.621
ETHAN:
You'll catch the next one.

33:20.595 --> 33:23.130
[ Door slams ]

33:23.165 --> 33:25.232
[ Monitor beeping ]

33:30.138 --> 33:32.973
WILLIAM:
There you go. There you go.

33:38.180 --> 33:40.348
Cut.

33:40.382 --> 33:43.884
GLADYS: Apparently,
she's an O.B. from New York.

33:43.919 --> 33:46.087
RAMONA:
You'd think she'd have more pizzazz.

33:46.121 --> 33:49.957
GLADYS: Not Manhattan... Ithaca.
It's practically Canada.

33:49.991 --> 33:51.792
[ Chuckles ]

33:51.827 --> 33:54.862
VIRGINIA:
She got her M.D. at Harvard,

33:54.896 --> 33:57.365
surgical fellowship with Hollinger
at Penn.

33:57.399 --> 33:59.900
I read his letter of recommendation,

33:59.935 --> 34:01.902
and it said,
if his eyes had been closed,

34:01.937 --> 34:04.171
he would not have known
she was a woman.

34:04.206 --> 34:06.173
RAMONA:
I can't tell with my eyes open.

34:06.208 --> 34:09.210
VIRGINIA:
I think it's inspiring, actually...

34:09.244 --> 34:12.847
A woman making a life
for herself on her own steam.

34:12.880 --> 34:16.350
I just can't believe they
put her in with the secretaries.

34:17.319 --> 34:19.920
GLADYS: Well, I don't care
where she went to school.

34:19.955 --> 34:21.922
No lady doctor's looking up my skirt.

34:21.956 --> 34:24.224
RAMONA:
Just the thought is revolting.

34:26.027 --> 34:28.362
[ Knocks on door ]

34:34.835 --> 34:36.437
VIRGINIA:
Hello?

34:39.674 --> 34:41.175
Libby?

34:46.047 --> 34:47.047
Lib?

34:47.081 --> 34:48.716
LIBBY:
[ Gasps ]

34:48.750 --> 34:51.018
VIRGINIA:
Lib?

34:51.052 --> 34:52.453
LIBBY:
Gini.

34:52.487 --> 34:54.088
VIRGINIA: The door was unlocked.
I don't want to intrude.

34:55.590 --> 34:57.591
<i>Bon appétit.</i>

34:57.626 --> 35:00.461
LIBBY:
Oh, it's beautiful.

35:00.495 --> 35:03.831
VIRGINIA: Well,
it looked better on the can.

35:05.434 --> 35:08.444
- You don't have to eat it.
- LIBBY: [ Laughs ]

35:09.738 --> 35:11.272
I don't know what to say.

35:13.575 --> 35:14.942
VIRGINIA:
It was Bill's idea.

35:14.976 --> 35:17.912
He's up to his elbows
in the quadruplet surgery,

35:17.946 --> 35:20.114
and he didn't want you to starve.

35:22.818 --> 35:27.121
I should probably get back
before I lose another sitter.

35:28.590 --> 35:30.724
Is there anything
I can do for you before I go?

35:32.861 --> 35:35.596
LIBBY:
Uh, there's a...

35:35.630 --> 35:38.732
There's a box up on
the top shelf of the closet.

35:40.769 --> 35:43.103
Green one.

35:53.482 --> 35:56.383
VIRGINIA:
Oh, they're darling.

36:00.722 --> 36:05.092
LIBBY: Take them and give them
to a... a mother from the ward.

36:05.126 --> 36:06.994
Someone should get some use
out of them.

36:07.028 --> 36:08.128
VIRGINIA:
Libby.

36:08.163 --> 36:10.364
LIBBY:
I found this in Bill's drawer.

36:10.398 --> 36:14.068
It's a statistical view
of female sterility.

36:14.102 --> 36:15.536
[ Breathes sharply ]

36:15.570 --> 36:19.240
For my condition, it's 8%.

36:19.274 --> 36:21.542
That's the number...

36:21.576 --> 36:24.478
An 8% chance
that I will ever be pregnant.

36:24.513 --> 36:31.452
All the tests and treatments...
Bill was just humoring me.

36:31.486 --> 36:32.553
[ Crying ]

36:32.587 --> 36:34.688
He deserves a family.

36:34.723 --> 36:38.926
But it's never gonna happen
because of me.

36:40.161 --> 36:41.662
VIRGINIA:
No. That's not true.

36:41.696 --> 36:44.298
LIBBY: And I'm so stupid.
I bought baby clothes.

36:44.332 --> 36:47.101
VIRGINIA: You're not stupid,
and it's not your fault. It's Bill.

36:56.311 --> 36:58.445
You don't have a condition, Libby.

36:58.480 --> 37:00.180
It's Bill. He's the one.

37:00.215 --> 37:03.851
He's the one with the problem.

37:03.885 --> 37:08.622
His sperm count.

37:08.657 --> 37:11.025
I saw your file.

37:20.335 --> 37:23.504
LIBBY:
Oh, my God.

37:23.538 --> 37:27.474
That's... Oh, no.

37:27.509 --> 37:29.610
[ Crying ]

37:29.644 --> 37:34.148
E-Ethan knows, too.
Everyone but me.

37:34.182 --> 37:37.318
VIRGINIA:
You can't say anything to Bill.

37:37.352 --> 37:39.420
Please, if he found out I told you...

37:39.454 --> 37:42.856
I'm so sorry, Libby. I am.

37:42.891 --> 37:48.195
It just... It doesn't seem right,
you blaming yourself.

38:00.709 --> 38:03.310
DALE:
I looked for you at the whorehouse.

38:10.118 --> 38:11.518
WILLIAM:
How do you know where I work?

38:11.553 --> 38:14.388
DALE:
I've been on campus once or twice.

38:14.422 --> 38:17.591
I was thinking about your science project.

38:17.626 --> 38:19.960
I figure I can help you.

38:19.995 --> 38:21.028
I know a lot of guys.

38:21.062 --> 38:22.796
They'd be glad to make a quick buck.

38:22.831 --> 38:24.598
WILLIAM:
I'm not interested in that.

38:24.633 --> 38:27.835
DALE: Not in that way.
You need warm bodies, right?

38:29.838 --> 38:32.573
WILLIAM:
Our needs have changed.

38:32.607 --> 38:34.341
DALE: Look, I never thought
that I'd be something

38:34.376 --> 38:36.276
a scientist would want to study.

38:36.311 --> 38:39.480
I like the idea.

38:39.514 --> 38:41.048
I want to be part of it.

38:43.518 --> 38:45.052
If it's about the money...

38:45.086 --> 38:47.154
WILLIAM: We're conducting a study
on normal human behavior.

38:50.025 --> 38:51.291
Dale:
You're saying I'm a deviant?

38:51.326 --> 38:54.895
WILLIAM: I'm saying you deviate...
statistically.

38:54.929 --> 38:58.365
Homosexual behavior lies outside the norm,

38:58.400 --> 39:01.067
therefore outside
the purview of our study.

39:02.270 --> 39:05.572
The medical community
would never accept it.

39:07.976 --> 39:09.376
DALE:
Okay.

39:12.180 --> 39:15.082
It's funny, I guess.

39:15.116 --> 39:19.386
You're the second person
in the medical community to fuck me.

39:19.421 --> 39:23.257
WILLIAM:
What do you mean?

39:23.291 --> 39:25.526
WOMAN: My eyesight is bad.
[ Door opens, closes ]

39:25.560 --> 39:26.860
MAN:
Why don't you wear glasses?

39:26.895 --> 39:28.495
- WOMAN: Glasses?!
- MAN: Sure. Why not?

39:28.530 --> 39:30.431
WOMAN:
'Cause they're terrible.

39:30.465 --> 39:32.299
[ Footsteps ]

39:37.572 --> 39:39.473
WILLIAM:
Libby?

39:42.043 --> 39:45.179
WOMAN: Of course,
they're not so bad on men.

39:46.481 --> 39:49.750
WILLIAM:
You're out of bed.

39:49.784 --> 39:51.585
LIBBY:
I didn't cook.

39:51.619 --> 39:53.120
You'll have to fend for yourself.

39:53.154 --> 39:55.556
WILLIAM:
I'm not hungry.

39:57.826 --> 39:59.593
How was your day?

40:03.031 --> 40:04.498
LIBBY:
Interesting.

40:04.532 --> 40:07.935
WILLIAM:
Mm. So was mine.

40:24.352 --> 40:26.653
I know these treatments are difficult.

40:26.688 --> 40:31.291
But you'll be yourself in a few days,

40:31.326 --> 40:33.060
I promise.

40:36.765 --> 40:40.667
God knows we all have
our cross to bear.

40:49.377 --> 40:51.845
BARTON:
Smile pretty for the camera.

40:51.880 --> 40:56.049
Bill, P.R.'s part of the job,
keeps the incubators running.

40:56.084 --> 40:59.286
Five minutes.
It's a necessary evil.

40:59.320 --> 41:00.654
[ Indistinct shouting ]

41:00.688 --> 41:02.923
MAN: Dr. Masters!
MAN 2: Dr. Masters!

41:04.125 --> 41:08.162
BARTON: 1 in 700,000...
Those are the odds for quadruplets.

41:08.196 --> 41:09.863
You're more likely
to get struck by lightning

41:09.898 --> 41:11.465
picking a four-leaf clover.

41:11.499 --> 41:13.333
And I'm not gonna tell you
the survival rate

41:13.368 --> 41:14.868
'cause it'll turn your hair white.

41:14.903 --> 41:18.438
It was the great fortune of
their mother and this hospital

41:18.473 --> 41:21.708
that we had a
one-in-a-million surgeon on hand

41:21.743 --> 41:24.678
to shepherd four perfect babies
into the world,

41:24.712 --> 41:29.316
my colleague and dear friend
Dr. William Masters.

41:29.350 --> 41:31.618
[ Applause ]

41:31.653 --> 41:34.087
MAN:
With the babies. Hand him a baby.

41:34.122 --> 41:36.673
MAN 2:
All right, get in nice and tight.

41:36.708 --> 41:38.525
- MAN: Smile.
- MAN 2: Right here.

41:38.560 --> 41:40.828
- MAN: One shot.
- MAN 2: Dr. Masters, right here.

41:40.862 --> 41:42.429
- MAN: Perfect.
- MAN 2: Very nice. Very nice.

41:42.463 --> 41:44.518
[ Baby cries ]
MAN: There you go.

41:49.771 --> 41:50.971
VIRGINIA:
Betty.

41:51.005 --> 41:52.940
[ Elevator bell dings ]

41:54.309 --> 41:56.577
They said you'd checked out.
I thought I'd missed you.

41:56.611 --> 41:59.613
BETTY:
Gene's pulling the wagon around.

41:59.647 --> 42:02.616
Ah, it's gonna slip right off.

42:02.650 --> 42:04.218
[ Chuckles ]

42:04.252 --> 42:05.886
Um...

42:05.920 --> 42:09.223
You know what he told me?

42:09.257 --> 42:13.527
He said, firstborn son, he wants
to name it after Bill Masters.

42:13.561 --> 42:17.364
He's practically painting
the nursery already.

42:17.398 --> 42:20.200
VIRGINIA:
Betty, lots of women can't have children.

42:20.235 --> 42:21.235
He will understand.

42:21.269 --> 42:22.703
If he really wants to marry you...

42:22.737 --> 42:26.306
BETTY: He won't understand
'cause I'm not gonna tell him.

42:26.341 --> 42:28.141
VIRGINIA:
What do you mean?

42:28.176 --> 42:33.380
BETTY: I'm gonna wear my white dress,
say my vows,

42:33.414 --> 42:37.551
and start my new life
with the Pretzel King.

42:37.585 --> 42:39.887
VIRGINIA:
You have other options.

42:39.921 --> 42:41.955
BETTY: Answering phones
for a buck 10 an hour?

42:41.990 --> 42:45.692
VIRGINIA: Maybe not that,
but...what about Helen?

42:48.496 --> 42:50.998
BETTY:
You want to get somewhere...

42:51.032 --> 42:53.033
You hitch your wagon to a man.

42:55.770 --> 42:57.905
That's what you're doing,

42:57.939 --> 43:00.340
following the doc around
like a cocker spaniel.

43:00.375 --> 43:03.243
VIRGINIA:
I am Dr. Masters' assistant.

43:03.278 --> 43:04.645
BETTY:
And because he's in love with you,

43:04.679 --> 43:06.613
you know you can use it
to your advantage.

43:06.648 --> 43:08.282
Don't act like you don't know
what I'm talking about.

43:08.316 --> 43:10.450
VIRGINIA:
That is absurd, Betty.

43:10.485 --> 43:11.718
GENE:
All right, let's shake a leg.

43:11.753 --> 43:13.754
I'm double-parked. Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

43:13.788 --> 43:15.822
- Oh, hi. Hi.
- VIRGINIA: Hi.

43:15.857 --> 43:18.358
GENE: You must be one
of Betty's girlfriends.

43:18.393 --> 43:19.793
Nice to meet you.

43:19.827 --> 43:21.595
Don't feel bad. She...
She doesn't introduce me to anyone.

43:21.629 --> 43:23.297
BETTY:
[ Laughs ]

43:23.331 --> 43:25.332
GENE: If I didn't know any better,
I'd say you were trying to hide me.

43:25.366 --> 43:28.368
BETTY: Oh, this here's Virginia,
the doc's secretary...

43:28.403 --> 43:29.970
Sorry.
[ Clears throat ]

43:30.004 --> 43:31.338
Assistant.

43:31.372 --> 43:36.109
Just another hard-working girl
doing the best she can.

43:36.144 --> 43:38.445
GENE: Good for you.
Nice to meet you.

43:38.479 --> 43:39.680
Ready?

43:39.714 --> 43:41.448
VIRGINIA:
Nice to meet you.

43:43.484 --> 43:45.619
GENE:
Hold on, there.

43:50.959 --> 43:53.527
- Oh, sorry, honey.
- BETTY: That's all right.

44:01.436 --> 44:04.171
LIBBY:
[ Sighs ]

44:04.205 --> 44:06.006
[ Door closes ]

44:06.040 --> 44:08.608
Well, you and Bill
make quite the team,

44:08.643 --> 44:09.810
wouldn't you say?

44:09.844 --> 44:12.412
ETHAN:
I don't know I'd say that.

44:13.648 --> 44:15.415
Hmm.
[ Clicks tongue ]

44:15.450 --> 44:17.517
That is the damndest thing.

44:17.552 --> 44:21.455
LIBBY: I think there's some information
you haven't shared with me, Ethan.

44:21.489 --> 44:25.125
ETHAN:
You're right. There is.

44:25.159 --> 44:26.727
[ Breathes deeply ]

44:26.761 --> 44:33.667
Bill thinks that he can do
everything by himself.

44:33.701 --> 44:36.370
But, technically,

44:36.404 --> 44:39.653
I'm the one
who got his wife pregnant.

44:41.509 --> 44:44.678
LIBBY:
[ Crying ]

44:44.712 --> 44:46.513
ETHAN:
[ Laughs ]

44:46.547 --> 44:48.982
[ Typewriter dings ]

44:49.017 --> 44:51.618
VIRGINIA:
[ Sighs ]

44:57.759 --> 45:01.128
[ Door opens, closes ]

45:01.162 --> 45:04.474
WILLIAM: Take these to the laundry,
no starch, and call Scully's office.

45:04.509 --> 45:06.584
Tell him I'm coming up to see him.

45:06.701 --> 45:08.668
VIRGINIA:
What's happening with the study?

45:10.613 --> 45:13.522
Because I'm a little confused.

45:13.557 --> 45:15.809
At night,
you treat me like a colleague,

45:15.843 --> 45:18.678
and here,
I seem to be your errand girl.

45:18.713 --> 45:21.882
WILLIAM: You're my secretary.
The job description is clear.

45:21.916 --> 45:23.050
VIRGINIA:
Not to me.

45:23.084 --> 45:24.951
I don't understand.

45:24.986 --> 45:28.221
If you think that I'm qualified
to conduct scientific research

45:28.256 --> 45:29.723
when it comes to the study,
how I am not qualified...

45:29.757 --> 45:32.191
WILLIAM: At the moment,
there is no study.

45:32.593 --> 45:35.929
The brothel is a disaster,
and the study is forbidden here,

45:35.963 --> 45:37.964
something you had a hand in,
I might remind you.

45:37.999 --> 45:39.533
Also, in case you've forgotten,

45:39.567 --> 45:42.436
uh, it has taken me over
20 years to get where I am...

45:42.470 --> 45:45.105
pre-med, medical school,
a grueling residency

45:45.139 --> 45:48.842
that finally landed me in
a world-class teaching hospital.

45:48.876 --> 45:52.212
Now, when you have that kind
of experience under your belt,

45:52.246 --> 45:55.749
you can tell me to take
the lab coats to the basement.

45:55.783 --> 45:58.351
Is that clear enough?

46:03.925 --> 46:06.392
[ Door closes ]

46:10.431 --> 46:14.468
What I'm saying is
I can't conduct my research in a brothel,

46:14.502 --> 46:16.336
and this study will suffocate

46:16.370 --> 46:19.272
without the respectability
of this hospital.

46:19.307 --> 46:21.775
BARTON: Dear God,
you are a dog with a bone.

46:21.809 --> 46:25.612
WILLIAM: I'm more like a cash
cow to you... to this hospital.

46:25.646 --> 46:27.581
And I'm on the front page,
in case you hadn't noticed.

46:27.615 --> 46:30.750
That kind of publicity
could buy you a new wing...

46:30.785 --> 46:33.653
instead of a long and costly
lawsuit over four dead newborns,

46:33.688 --> 46:36.123
which is where you were headed
until I stepped in.

46:36.157 --> 46:37.757
BARTON:
Which is why I put you on the case.

46:37.792 --> 46:40.594
WILLIAM: I could just as easily,
uh, tell the press the truth...

46:40.628 --> 46:42.362
that you actually
put a fellow on the case.

46:42.396 --> 46:45.332
BARTON:
Do not fuck with me, Bill!

46:45.366 --> 46:47.134
Because when it comes
to throwing weight around,

46:47.168 --> 46:49.836
I will crush you into dust,

46:49.871 --> 46:52.139
even if I don't want to.

46:52.173 --> 46:55.642
Now, four babies are downstairs

46:55.676 --> 46:58.044
that wouldn't be here
if it wasn't for you.

46:58.079 --> 47:00.680
It was a good day.
Go home to your wife.

47:00.715 --> 47:04.451
Come back tomorrow
to the job you were meant to do.

47:04.485 --> 47:05.619
WILLIAM:
[ Sighs ]

47:05.653 --> 47:07.487
You know, I met a young man
at the brothel...

47:07.522 --> 47:10.423
A prostitute, a homosexual.

47:10.458 --> 47:11.858
He came to see me last night.

47:11.893 --> 47:13.160
BARTON:
For Christ's sake, Bill.

47:13.194 --> 47:16.062
WILLIAM: He opened my eyes
to a few, uh, realities.

47:16.097 --> 47:18.532
BARTON: I mean it...
Spare me the lurid details.

47:18.566 --> 47:19.933
WILLIAM:
The men who pay to see him...

47:19.967 --> 47:22.769
They're not convicts or reprobates.

47:22.803 --> 47:25.639
They're not degenerates.

47:25.673 --> 47:27.607
They're family men,

47:27.642 --> 47:33.079
